theorem frontier_closure_subset_frontier {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    frontier (closure A) ⊆ frontier A := by
  intro x hx
  -- `hx` gives `x ∈ closure (closure A)` and `x ∈ closure ((closure A)ᶜ)`.
  rcases hx with ⟨hx_cl_cl, hx_cl_compl⟩
  -- Simplify the first membership.
  have hx_clA : x ∈ closure A := by
    simpa [closure_closure] using hx_cl_cl
  -- Show that `x` also lies in `closure (Aᶜ)`.
  have h_subset : (closure A)ᶜ ⊆ (Aᶜ : Set X) := by
    intro y hy
    by_contra hAy
    -- If `y ∈ A`, then `y ∈ closure A`, contradicting `hy`.
    have : y ∈ closure A := subset_closure hAy
    exact hy this
  have hx_clAc : x ∈ closure (Aᶜ) :=
    (closure_mono h_subset) hx_cl_compl
  -- Combine the two facts to conclude.
  exact And.intro hx_clA hx_clAc

theorem closure_union_interior_eq_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (A ∪ interior A) = closure A := by
  apply subset_antisymm
  · -- First, prove `closure (A ∪ interior A) ⊆ closure A`.
    have h_subset : (A ∪ interior A : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
      intro x hx
      cases hx with
      | inl hA      => exact subset_closure hA
      | inr hIntA   => exact subset_closure (interior_subset hIntA)
    exact closure_mono h_subset
  · -- Second, prove `closure A ⊆ closure (A ∪ interior A)`.
    have h_subset : (A : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ interior A := by
      intro x hx
      exact Or.inl hx
    exact closure_mono h_subset
